title: Live: Smith out for duck, CA XI in hunt
text:
Matador Cup 2015: live coverage of Tasmania v Cricket Australia XI, NSW v Western Australia FOX SPORTS Matador Cup 2015: live coverage of Tasmania v Cricket Australia XI, NSW v Western Australia FOX SPORTS Mitch Marsh dismisses Steve Smith for duck 0:40 
Cricket: Watch Mitch Marsh dismiss the Australian captain Steve Smith for 0 in Western Australia's one-day match against New South Wales. October 10th 2015 8 minutes ago /video/video.news.com.au/Sport/Cricket/Highlights/ 
THE Cricket Australia XI is a strong chance of posting its first ever victory, while Australia captain Steve Smith was dismissed for a duck on an eventful day of Matador Cup action. 
The dayâ€™s first match saw the CA XI beat its previous highest batting total of 79 by a whopping 162 runs, finishing on 7-241 from their 50 overs against Tasmania. 
In reply the Tigers were in big trouble with 10 overs remaining, having been reduced to 5-167. 
Needing a further 75 runs from 60 balls, they were relying heavily on renowned finisher James Faulkner, who was on 13 not out. 
In the match at Blacktown International Sports Park, New South Wales made a strong start in the grand final replay against Western Australia. 
After 34 overs the Blues were 2-161, with Ed Cowan and Shane Watson at the crease. Other Stories
